# UI Text Must Use i18n Keys

- Never hardcode visible UI text in frontend source files.
- All user-visible labels, headings, button text, placeholders, tooltips, table headers, empty states, and status messages must use `t("<key>", "<english default>")`.
- Every new UI text must be added to `frontend/src/i18n/translations.json` with both:
  - `text.en` (English)
  - `text.de` (German)
- Keep `label.en`/`label.de` metadata for translation-admin readability.
- Reuse existing keys when semantics match; only add new keys when needed.
- Avoid embedding translated literals in helper utilities; pass translated text from components/hooks.

## Required Check Before Finish

- Scan changed frontend files for hardcoded visible strings.
- If a visible literal remains, move it to `translations.json` and replace with `t(...)`.
